House Resolution 840
By: Representative Erwin of the 32nd
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Laurie Erwin for her outstanding dedication and
2 accomplishments in golf, including her remarkable achievement of a hole-in-one, and for her
3 commitment to inspiring the next generation of leaders; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, Laurie Erwin, a proud native of Homer, Georgia, has demonstrated exceptional
5 talent, dedication, and passion for the sport of golf; and
6 WHEREAS, on June 29, 2024, at Chimney Oaks Golf Club in Homer, Georgia, Laurie Erwin
7 achieved the extraordinary feat of a hole-in-one on a distance of 89 yards while using a
8 pitching wedge, a testament to her skill and precision; and
9 WHEREAS, her accomplishment and enthusiasm were witnessed by her proud husband,
10 Chairman Chris Erwin, Representative of House District 32, marking the moment not only
11 as a sporting achievement but also as a cherished family memory; and
12 WHEREAS, Laurie Erwin's athletic ability, combined with her unwavering dedication and
13 determination to the sport, continues to inspire those around her, showcasing the power of
14 perseverance and the joy of the game of golf; and
