15 WHEREAS, beyond her sporting achievements, Laurie Erwin is deeply committed to
16 inspiring young leaders and dedicating her time to mentoring the youth of Georgia,
17 particularly through the House Page Program, where she actively works to encourage and
18 guide young individuals in their pursuit of excellence and leadership; and
19 WHEREAS, through her involvement in the House Page Program, Laurie Erwin has played
20 a pivotal role in shaping the future of Georgia's youth, imparting the values of responsibility,
21 integrity, and civic duty to the next generation of leaders; and
22 WHEREAS, Laurie Erwin has become a role model for young athletes and leaders alike,
23 demonstrating the values of hard work, integrity, and service to the community; and
24 WHEREAS, Laurie Erwin's contributions to the sport and her community bring great pride
25 to the State of Georgia as she sets an example of excellence and encourages future
26 generations of golfers and leaders.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend Laurie Erwin upon her exceptional
29 achievement for her ongoing contributions to the sport of golf, her community, and the State
30 of Georgia as well as her commitment to shaping and inspiring the leaders of tomorrow.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
33 Laurie Erwin.
